#: ../../manual/compositing/types/color/bright_contrast.rst:52
msgid ""
"Either of these nodes will scale the values back to normal range. In the "
"example image, we want to amp up the specular pass. The bottom thread shows "
"what happens if we do not clamp the values; the specular pass has valued "
"much less than one in the dark areas; when added to the medium gray, it "
"makes black. Passing the brightened image through either the Map Value or "
"the Color Ramp node produces the desired effect."
msgstr ""

